Gigabyte has revealed new J-series and N-series mini-ITX motherboards which feature embedded Intel CPUs. The boards include Intel Pentium Silver and Intel Celeron processors, with fanless cooling solutions. The processors are built on Intelâ€™s Gemini Lake architecture and support 4K video, NVMe storage, and DDR4 memory at 2,400MHz. The CPUs have a TDP of 10W and are available in dual-core and quad-core models. There is currently no pricing or launch date information for the new Gigabyte motherboards.